00:50:58,889 --> 00:51:02,225
You had time to think
long and hard in prison, Mossie.

569
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:05,687
You don't want to end up
on the wrong side of history again, no?

570
00:51:06,063 --> 00:51:09,441
An embittered old man
with not a penny to your name.

571
00:51:09,525 --> 00:51:11,025
You've so much to live for.

572
00:51:11,110 --> 00:51:14,070
You've got a lovely spouse.
Isn't that right, Angela?

573
00:51:14,864 --> 00:51:18,158
And I could get you
a job for life in the Council.

574
00:51:19,160 --> 00:51:24,164
Watch your children
grow up in security. Educated.

575
00:51:25,666 --> 00:51:27,709
You're at a crossroads, Mossie.

576
00:51:29,462 --> 00:51:35,884
Listen to me. You could even get
little Katie back from Scotland. Hmm?

577
00:51:40,431 --> 00:51:43,600
- Would you like a scone, Father?
- Thank you. Thank you, Angela.

578
00:51:45,186 --> 00:51:47,312
Here's a picture of our little Katie.

579
00:51:47,396 --> 00:51:49,397
Oh, isn't she a dote?

580
00:51:49,482 --> 00:51:52,817
- Beautiful little girl.
- Just like her mammy.

581
00:51:52,902 --> 00:51:55,445
- Thank you, Father.
- You must miss her terribly.

582
00:51:55,529 --> 00:51:57,155
Very, very much.

583
00:51:59,408 --> 00:52:02,952
Oh, we have the Redemptorist Fathers
coming to the parish for a mission.

584
00:52:03,037 --> 00:52:06,247
What if I was to bring around
a doctor of divinity into your house,

585
00:52:06,332 --> 00:52:09,083
to explain to you where Gralton
is leading you astray?

586
00:52:09,502 --> 00:52:13,797
What if I was to bring a doctor of
economics round to your house, Father,

587
00:52:14,173 --> 00:52:16,800
and explain to you
where you're going astray?

588
00:52:17,301 --> 00:52:19,552
Loyalty is a noble thing,

589
00:52:19,637 --> 00:52:24,349
but misplaced loyalty,
for a man with children, is a tragedy.

