And hop over and... hop over and...

599
00:52:57,883 --> 00:53:01,678
Hop stop. And one, two, three...

600
00:53:01,762 --> 00:53:03,763
Marie!

601
00:53:05,558 --> 00:53:08,393
I'm sorry I'm late. I...
I couldn't get on my bike.

602
00:53:08,477 --> 00:53:10,353
- What's wrong?
- I'm sorry.

603
00:53:10,437 --> 00:53:12,313
- It's OK.
- Marie, what's the matter?

604
00:53:12,398 --> 00:53:16,025
- I couldn't get on my bike.
- What's wrong? What's wrong?

605
00:53:16,110 --> 00:53:18,778
I didn't want to miss the class.

606
00:53:18,863 --> 00:53:20,905
- Marie...
- There's no worries.

607
00:53:20,990 --> 00:53:23,908
Jimmy, get her a chair.
Marie, what happened to your back?

608
00:53:23,993 --> 00:53:26,244
Come on, have a seat.

609
00:53:26,328 --> 00:53:29,289
What's the matter?

610
00:53:30,833 --> 00:53:35,128
"Lay the lash upon their backs."
That's what the Bishop of Galway said.

611
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:40,508
They make the blood boil,
these hooligans with a cross in their hand.

612
00:53:40,926 --> 00:53:44,804
Closing in like hounds. There's talks
of bringing in the Redemptorists

613
00:53:44,889 --> 00:53:47,390
to preach fire and thunder for a week.

614
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:50,268
Father Sheridan
came to the shop.

615
00:53:52,438 --> 00:53:55,481
He said...
he said he'd organise a boycott.

616
00:53:55,566 --> 00:53:57,567
- What?
- It's your livelihood.

617
00:53:57,651 --> 00:54:00,528
- He could ruin us.
- What did Brendan say?

618
00:54:03,115 --> 00:54:05,491
He doesn't want me coming here anymore.

619
00:54:08,579 --> 00:54:12,707
I'm so sorry,
but I can't teach the classes any more.

620
00:54:15,461 --> 00:54:17,378
I'm sorry.

621
00:54:17,463 --> 00:54:20,256
He's after being in the houses
of most of the lads we know.

622
00:54:20,341 --> 00:54:22,175
It's starting to happen
in other parishes.

623
00:54:22,259 --> 00:54:24,135
They're all doing the same thing.

624
00:54:24,345 --> 00:54:26,346
Father Sheridan
came up to see my father,

625
00:54:26,430 --> 00:54:28,389
with the Knights of Saint Columbanus.

626
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:31,100
They were scheming away.

627
00:54:31,352 --> 00:54:33,937
And they'll have your da
and the fascists on one side,

628
00:54:34,021 --> 00:54:36,731
and the bloody Dohertys
of this world on the other.

629
00:54:36,941 --> 00:54:39,567
At a safe, deniable distance, you know.

630
00:54:39,652 --> 00:54:45,406
At each other's throats, but only united
by a mutual hatred of us.

631
00:54:45,866 --> 00:54:48,993
We've still got lots of support
out there.

632
00:54:49,078 --> 00:54:50,870
People are stopping me all the time.

633
00:54:50,955 --> 00:54:55,083
And, listen, half those lads in
Fianna Fail, they think he's a fanatic.

634
00:54:55,167 --> 00:54:57,418
Spit licks who will genuflect
when the time comes.

635
00:54:57,503 --> 00:55:01,005
They're good lads, Sean.
And some of 'em were at the dance here.

636
00:55:01,090 --> 00:55:02,966
My old brigade, most of them.

637
00:55:03,050 --> 00:55:05,343
And the unemployed movement,
they're with us.

638
00:55:05,594 --> 00:55:07,929
Lots of the parents,
they're still solid...

639
00:55:08,013 --> 00:55:12,350
For how long, Tommy?
He called us antichrists!

640
00:55:12,434 --> 00:55:15,311
Look, we need to see it
from his point of view. Right?

641
00:55:15,396 --> 00:55:18,564
We're in his parish,
so he must confront us.

642
00:55:18,649 --> 00:55:22,193
And his fellow priests, bishops
and the entire Catholic community

643
00:55:22,277 --> 00:55:24,988
are all watching him,
so there's pressure on him too.

644
00:55:25,072 --> 00:55:26,823
So we have to get him off our backs,

645
00:55:26,907 --> 00:55:29,450
without him losing face
before his supporters.

646
00:55:31,036 --> 00:55:36,207
What if... What if we ask the Reverend
Father to be on our board of trustees?

647
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:37,333
Jesus.

648
00:55:37,418 --> 00:55:41,379
We can't be antichrists then.
We've always said everyone's welcome.

649
00:55:41,463 --> 00:55:44,549
If it continues like this, you know,
we'll have an empty hall.

650
00:55:45,092 --> 00:55:49,262
I feel for the lads. There's nothing
for them after all this work.

651
00:55:49,346 --> 00:55:53,891
I'm becoming fed up of
being a pragmatist in church, you know.

652
00:55:54,018 --> 00:55:57,395
Here's this young girl beside me,
she's been beaten because of them,

653
00:55:57,479 --> 00:55:59,147
and she shows up here the next day.

654
00:55:59,231 --> 00:56:01,274
We have to be very careful.

655
00:56:01,358 --> 00:56:05,695
Those people don't just join.
They come to take over.

656
00:56:26,967 --> 00:56:28,509
Holy Moses.

657
00:56:28,594 --> 00:56:30,887
- No, it's only me.
- What do you want?

658
00:56:31,346 --> 00:56:35,183
I've come to get me devil's horns
put on. Is Father Sheridan in?

659
00:56:35,267 --> 00:56:36,809
He is. Come in.

660
00:56:42,483 --> 00:56:43,816
Well, I'll be damned.

661
00:56:43,901 --> 00:56:46,944
Don't lose hope, Father.
There's still time to repent.

662
00:56:47,029 --> 00:56:51,574
Oh, is that so? Well, as you're here,
you might as well come in.

663
00:57:01,126 --> 00:57:04,420
We want to invite you to join
our board of trustees who run the hall.

664
00:57:04,505 --> 00:57:09,217
I'm hopeful that once you come along and
see what we're doing with your own eyes,

665
00:57:09,301 --> 00:57:11,177
we can put all this behind us.

666
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:16,015
So, I am to be the odd man out
among your, er, hand-picked comrades.

667
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:19,102
And no doubt when it comes
to choosing reading material,

668
00:57:19,186 --> 00:57:22,021
- there'll be... There'll be a vote?
- Can you not at least...

669
00:57:22,106 --> 00:57:24,065
No, it's a gracious offering,
Mr. Gralton.

670
00:57:24,149 --> 00:57:25,900
At a time when a quarter of the country

671
00:57:25,984 --> 00:57:28,611
is planning to travel to Dublin
for the Eucharistic Congress,

672
00:57:28,695 --> 00:57:32,990
and the other 75 percent will be
tuning into the radio from Athlone,

673
00:57:33,408 --> 00:57:38,162
a country supremely united
in faith, in love and respect,

674
00:57:38,247 --> 00:57:40,915
for Christ's representative on earth.

675
00:57:41,667 --> 00:57:43,668
Have a look at that painting.

676
00:57:45,712 --> 00:57:50,341
Democratic Irish State,
true to its traditions.

677
00:57:50,425 --> 00:57:51,509
In harmony with its people

678
00:57:51,593 --> 00:57:56,806
and under the guidance of
the one true universal Apostolic Church.

679
00:57:57,182 --> 00:58:02,019
That is the natural way. Now, sit down.

680
00:58:04,398 --> 00:58:08,693
You know my family are believers.
My sister is a nun.

681
00:58:08,777 --> 00:58:13,030
I said the rosary in solidarity with
fighters during the War of Independence.

682
00:58:13,115 --> 00:58:16,242
"Love thy neighbour"
is revered in my book too.

683
00:58:16,326 --> 00:58:19,745
In our hall, we respect
freedom of religion and conscience.

684
00:58:20,038 --> 00:58:23,499
Tell that to the Soviets who have
murdered Christians in their thousands.

685
00:58:23,584 --> 00:58:26,502
And don't get me started
on Joseph Stalin's secret prisons,

686
00:58:26,587 --> 00:58:28,588
and that famine that's on the horizon.

687
00:58:28,672 --> 00:58:32,758
Don't get me started either, Father.
That is a long debate to be had.

688
00:58:32,843 --> 00:58:36,596
But today, can we talk about the hall
and just listen to what we have to say?

689
00:58:36,680 --> 00:58:39,765
I am not a politician.
No deals in dingy corners.

690
00:58:39,850 --> 00:58:43,269
No half measures. No compromise.
There's no...

691
00:58:43,353 --> 00:58:46,063
A question, please, Reverend Father.

692
00:58:46,148 --> 00:58:49,901
When was the last time
you really listened to someone else?

693
00:58:51,486 --> 00:58:54,780
Actually,
it was last night at confessions.

694
00:58:55,282 --> 00:59:00,036
I listen to the innermost secrets
and fears of our community.

695
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:05,041
People open their hearts to me.
Not the man, but the priest,

696
00:59:05,834 --> 00:59:09,712
in a way unknown to your... imagination.

697
00:59:10,130 --> 00:59:12,798
Look at these hands, Father.

698
00:59:12,883 --> 00:59:15,009
Dirt under the fingernails.

699
00:59:15,093 --> 00:59:16,886
I'm no scholar.

700
00:59:16,970 --> 00:59:20,640
I've been a soldier, a sailor,
a docker, a miner,

701
00:59:20,724 --> 00:59:22,975
on the seas and underground.

702
00:59:23,060 --> 00:59:26,395
I've seen much and made many a mistake,

703
00:59:26,897 --> 00:59:29,774
but despite all our flaws,

704
00:59:29,858 --> 00:59:33,945
I believe in my neighbour,
my fellow man, my class.

705
00:59:34,029 --> 00:59:38,115
Meeting up and struggling
to understand our lives as best we can.

706
00:59:38,200 --> 00:59:42,370
On our own, in isolation, we perish.

707
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:44,789
The hall is a safe space

708
00:59:44,873 --> 00:59:50,419
where we can think, talk,
learn, listen and laugh and dance.

709
00:59:50,504 --> 00:59:51,879
It's a good place.

710
00:59:51,964 --> 00:59:55,007
If I were a believer like you,
I'd call it a holy place.

711
00:59:55,509 --> 00:59:57,510
It brings out the best in us.

712
00:59:58,387 --> 01:00:01,472
Don't be frightened.
Come along, meet us.

713
01:00:01,556 --> 01:00:04,684
Talk to us, question us,
but work with us.

714
01:00:04,768 --> 01:00:07,311
There is enough misery
in the world already.

715
01:00:08,605 --> 01:00:11,065
Oh, you are a believer, Jimmy.

716
01:00:11,817 --> 01:00:13,192
Yes, you are.

717
01:00:13,777 --> 01:00:17,571
And part of me holds you
in very high esteem.

718
01:00:17,698 --> 01:00:21,909
So, yes, I will come along
and listen to you and your trustees,

719
01:00:21,994 --> 01:00:25,663
once you have brought me
the title deeds to the hall,

720
01:00:25,747 --> 01:00:29,458
and have them transferred over
to Holy Mother Church.

721
01:00:34,381 --> 01:00:39,510
I take it back, Father. You do listen,
but only when we're on our knees.

722
01:00:52,316 --> 01:00:56,652
A flight of Free State aeroplanes
flying in the form of a cross

723
01:00:56,778 --> 01:00:58,571
escorted the special boat.

724
01:01:01,116 --> 01:01:04,618
And then Cardinal Lauri stepped ashore,

725
01:01:04,745 --> 01:01:09,623
the first Papal Legate to land
in Ireland for over two centuries.

726
01:01:11,126 --> 01:01:13,586
Accompanied by Mr. de Valera
and his ministers...

727
01:01:14,921 --> 01:01:16,672
he inspected the Guard of Honour,

728
01:01:16,757 --> 01:01:20,676
followed by his retinue of
Vatican officials in Elizabethan dress.

729
01:01:21,845 --> 01:01:23,304
The streets along the route

730
01:01:23,430 --> 01:01:27,600
had been thronged for hours
before the Papal Legate was due,

731
01:01:27,684 --> 01:01:30,436
and he received a tumultuous reception.

732
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:15,064
Sweeney...

733
01:02:16,733 --> 01:02:18,484
There's Gralton!

734
01:02:18,568 --> 01:02:21,821
Mossie Maguire. Tommy Gilroy. You rats!

735
01:02:21,905 --> 01:02:24,198
Move on, you fascists.

736
01:02:24,324 --> 01:02:27,410
- You shouldn't be here.
- Sweeney, get out and let us watch...

737
01:02:27,494 --> 01:02:29,286
I said get out and let us watch the film.

738
01:02:29,371 --> 01:02:32,498
- Antichrist!
- Atherton.

739
01:02:35,502 --> 01:02:39,463
In spite of dungeon, fire and sword

740
01:02:39,548 --> 01:02:42,049
Sing, boys!

741
01:02:42,175 --> 01:02:45,052
Don't encourage them.
Watch the film, ignore 'em.

742
01:02:46,430 --> 01:02:49,515
Get out, Sweeney. We've watched
your propaganda, now go home.

743
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:52,726
Faith of our fathers, holy faith!

744
01:02:52,853 --> 01:02:56,897
- We will be true to thee till death
- Thank you.

745
01:02:57,023 --> 01:02:59,650
We will be true to thee till death

746
01:02:59,734 --> 01:03:01,318
Yeah, go on. Go on home.

747
01:03:01,403 --> 01:03:04,530
Get back to your Yankee friends,
you Red bastards!

748
01:03:17,043 --> 01:03:18,752
Whoa there, Dixie. Whoa, whoa.

749
01:03:18,879 --> 01:03:20,754
- Good man, Mossie.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

750
01:03:20,881 --> 01:03:24,550
Mossie, I've left my bike at the hall,
so I'll make my own way home.

751
01:03:25,469 --> 01:03:28,804
Youse mind yourselves, then.
They'll be looking for us.

752
01:03:28,889 --> 01:03:31,223
The witch hunt has started.
You two, be careful.

753
01:03:31,308 --> 01:03:33,893
Likewise. Good luck.
Look after yourselves.

754
01:03:35,896 --> 01:03:37,354
Get on, Dixie.

755
01:03:48,909 --> 01:03:50,242
Lock the door.

756
01:04:03,798 --> 01:04:06,425
- Keep your back turned.
- What?

757
01:04:27,364 --> 01:04:30,950
- I hope you're not looking.
- I wouldn't dare.

758
01:04:49,302 --> 01:04:50,970
You can look now.

759
01:05:01,147 --> 01:05:02,648
Fits perfectly.

760
01:05:07,320 --> 01:05:09,154
Why wouldn't it?

761
01:07:45,478 --> 01:07:48,063
You take my breath away.

762
01:07:50,817 --> 01:07:53,736
I think my heart
is going to break.

763
01:08:26,436 --> 01:08:28,228
Firstly,
I just wanted to thank you all

764
01:08:28,354 --> 01:08:31,940
for agreeing to meet with us today.
It's about a fella called Milmoe.

765
01:08:32,358 --> 01:08:37,070
Molly, that's the wife, there outside.
Erm, he's in a dire situation.

766
01:08:38,281 --> 01:08:40,699
He's looking for the Roscommon IRA
to help him.

767
01:08:41,117 --> 01:08:44,745
He's been forcibly evicted out of
his cottage on the Kingston estate.

768
01:08:45,789 --> 01:08:48,874
We had an angry meeting last night,
a big split.

769
01:08:49,292 --> 01:08:51,919
A third of us want to
reinstate him by force.

770
01:08:52,754 --> 01:08:56,548
A third want nothing to do with it.
And there's a third sitting on the fence.

771
01:08:56,883 --> 01:08:59,301
And he has
the best of connections.

772
01:08:59,385 --> 01:09:02,054
He has the guards. He has the army.

773
01:09:02,138 --> 01:09:04,556
He has the ranchers and the politicians.

774
01:09:04,641 --> 01:09:08,143
Not just the local ones,
but the bigwigs.

775
01:09:08,770 --> 01:09:11,146
There's some tough boys on this estate.

776
01:09:11,231 --> 01:09:13,857
His agent's a vicious bastard.
A bad egg.

777
01:09:13,942 --> 01:09:16,610
That's a feckin' handful, all right.
Bejaysus, yeah.

778
01:09:16,736 --> 01:09:19,696
 But there's 5 children
out there on the side of the road,

779
01:09:19,781 --> 01:09:22,157
and a woman outside this hall
bawling her eyes out,

780
01:09:22,242 --> 01:09:24,451
unless any of you want to
go out and see her.

781
01:09:25,328 --> 01:09:28,872
Now... things aren't too great
with ourselves.

782
01:09:28,957 --> 01:09:31,375
We're not as strong
as what we used to be.

783
01:09:31,459 --> 01:09:33,585
Truth be told, there's very few of us.

784
01:09:34,254 --> 01:09:36,588
Even our OC doesn't even know
we're here today.

785
01:09:36,673 --> 01:09:39,216
But you know what we know,
what's going on out there.

786
01:09:39,300 --> 01:09:41,677
There's a queer fear out there
amongst the people,

787
01:09:41,761 --> 01:09:44,137
and something's going to have
to be done about it.

788
01:09:45,515 --> 01:09:47,641
So, what do you want from us?

789
01:09:47,767 --> 01:09:49,852
We need your help
to reinstate them.

790
01:09:49,936 --> 01:09:52,855
There'll be a big turnout
if we can spread the word

791
01:09:52,939 --> 01:09:56,108
that Jimmy Gralton and his supporters
from Leitrim are coming.

792
01:09:56,192 --> 01:10:00,487
It isn't just about the reinstatement.
It's much more important than that.

793
01:10:00,613 --> 01:10:03,198
It's about the message we send out there
to the wider community.

794
01:10:03,283 --> 01:10:06,535
Think about what could be done.
That's why it's important.

795
01:10:07,120 --> 01:10:10,289
And that's why it's important, Jimmy,
that you speak to the crowd.

796
01:10:10,373 --> 01:10:14,126
- Can someone else not speak?
- No, it has to be Jimmy.

797
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:16,879
He's got the words, he's got the spake.

798
01:10:16,963 --> 01:10:19,840
He's got the confidence and trust
of the people out there,

799
01:10:19,966 --> 01:10:22,342
and with all due respect
to the rest of you here,

800
01:10:22,468 --> 01:10:25,137
you wouldn't pull a quarter of
the support of what Jimmy would.

801
01:10:25,221 --> 01:10:27,139
It has to be Jimmy that speaks.

802
01:10:28,558 --> 01:10:29,975
What do you think?

803
01:10:30,059 --> 01:10:34,771
Well, I think that every journalist
from the local press will be there.

804
01:10:34,856 --> 01:10:39,234
I think they'll note your words,
which will spread like wildfire,

805
01:10:39,319 --> 01:10:43,280
and be seen as a direct challenge to
landed estates throughout the country.

806
01:10:43,364 --> 01:10:45,324
That's why we must win this one.

807
01:10:45,408 --> 01:10:48,035
Yeah, and why...
and why they need to.

808
01:10:48,161 --> 01:10:49,786
You know what'll happen, Jimmy.

809
01:10:49,871 --> 01:10:52,372
It's hard to judge, but...

810
01:10:52,498 --> 01:10:54,374
they could come after you again, Jimmy.

811
01:10:54,500 --> 01:10:57,085
No, there's no "could"
about it, Dessie.

812
01:10:57,378 --> 01:10:59,546
They will. Of course they will.

813
01:10:59,672 --> 01:11:02,174
And they'll close down the hall.
It's suicide.

814
01:11:02,258 --> 01:11:04,927
Well, we don't know that
for certain, Mossie.

815
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:07,429
I mean, you know,
it's not the time for pessimism.

816
01:11:07,513 --> 01:11:10,515
I-I'm not a pessimist.
I'm a realist.

817
01:11:10,850 --> 01:11:13,435
I know the way these bastards are.

818
01:11:14,020 --> 01:11:20,692
I'm on a, still, on a blacklist, Sean,
for 10 years. 10 feckin' years!

819
01:11:20,777 --> 01:11:24,488
No, I know that
and, look, it's an opportunity.

820
01:11:24,572 --> 01:11:27,157
Here are 5 children out on the street

821
01:11:27,241 --> 01:11:31,703
from a lord who has thousands of acres
inherited from foreign invasion.

822
01:11:31,788 --> 01:11:34,122
I mean, who has the right to the land?

823
01:11:34,207 --> 01:11:36,917
We know who has the right to the land.
We know that.

824
01:11:37,043 --> 01:11:39,670
Is it... Is it the rich man on his own,

825
01:11:39,754 --> 01:11:42,339
or is it the families
that live and work that land?

826
01:11:42,423 --> 01:11:46,802
What is the burning issue
up and down this country?

827
01:11:46,886 --> 01:11:51,264
The breakup of large estates
to landless labourers.

828
01:11:51,391 --> 01:11:52,766
- D'you know?
- I do.

829
01:11:52,892 --> 01:11:55,018
I don't think we're gonna get
a better chance.

830
01:11:55,103 --> 01:11:57,437
- And we shouldn't let it pass.
- That's right.

831
01:11:57,563 --> 01:12:02,359
This is critical.
People are angry. They're desperate.

832
01:12:02,443 --> 01:12:06,113
There's no money coming from family
in America because of the Depression.

833
01:12:06,239 --> 01:12:07,823
We should strike now, James.

834
01:12:07,907 --> 01:12:09,908
Think before we leap.

835
01:12:09,993 --> 01:12:12,661
- We forget the bishops at our peril.
- Exactly.

836
01:12:12,745 --> 01:12:15,706
They've never been stronger
after the Eucharistic Congress.

837
01:12:15,790 --> 01:12:19,835
You saw the crowds in Dublin.
They've the Government in their pocket.

838
01:12:19,919 --> 01:12:21,336
They'll go for the kill.

839
01:12:21,421 --> 01:12:23,213
We have supporters.

840
01:12:23,297 --> 01:12:27,384
There are thousands of landless
labourers outside these estates.

841
01:12:27,468 --> 01:12:30,137
The rich are nervous. Fearful.

842
01:12:30,263 --> 01:12:32,014
We have to keep pushing.

843
01:12:32,098 --> 01:12:34,891
Ruari's right. And let me ask you this.

844
01:12:34,976 --> 01:12:39,646
What is the feckin' point of this hall
if we do not support these people?

845
01:12:39,772 --> 01:12:42,399
We built this hall
with our own hands.

846
01:12:42,483 --> 01:12:46,987
We put our lives into it.
Heart and soul. Everything we had.

847
01:12:47,113 --> 01:12:52,451
It's not just a building,
it's... it's what we are.

848
01:12:52,535 --> 01:12:54,870
It's everything.
And we have to protect it.

849
01:12:54,954 --> 01:12:58,123
Not just for ourselves,
but for the youngsters coming after.

850
01:12:58,207 --> 01:13:02,085
And I know from bitter experience that
if you bite off more than you can chew,

851
01:13:02,170 --> 01:13:03,545
you'll feckin' choke.

852
01:13:03,629 --> 01:13:05,630
Exactly.

853
01:13:05,715 --> 01:13:09,801
I'm sorry, lads, but that's my fear too.

854
01:13:10,178 --> 01:13:12,054
It's time for caution.

855
01:13:12,972 --> 01:13:15,265
My heart goes out
to that woman in the cart.

856
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:17,559
They're too strong at the moment.

857
01:13:17,643 --> 01:13:20,437
They're too wild.
We have to bide our time.

858
01:13:20,521 --> 01:13:21,688
I agree.

859
01:13:21,814 --> 01:13:25,150
I don't think Jimmy should talk.
He shouldn't speak this time.

860
01:13:25,234 --> 01:13:27,861
For Christ's sake, though,
they're coming after us anyway.

861
01:13:28,404 --> 01:13:30,363
I mean, there's no denying that.

862
01:13:31,491 --> 01:13:34,159
- I say we support this family.
- Stand together.

863
01:13:34,660 --> 01:13:37,996
Oonagh. You've hardly said a word.

864
01:13:57,892 --> 01:13:59,810
- Mam.
- Hello, Jimmy.

865
01:14:09,153 --> 01:14:13,824
Sacred Heart of Jesus, Jimmy, can you
thread this needle for me, please?

866
01:14:16,661 --> 01:14:20,413
My eyesight is getting so bad,
and I need to mend your shirt.

867
01:14:30,716 --> 01:14:32,509
- Here.
- Thank you.

868
01:14:32,593 --> 01:14:35,720
If they drive me out again, Mam,
I want you to come with me.

869
01:14:37,223 --> 01:14:40,058
I mean it, Mam.
I'll find a place for us both.

870
01:14:42,854 --> 01:14:46,273
Maybe somewhere easier to manage.
Not so isolated.

871
01:14:51,571 --> 01:14:52,737
Well?

872
01:14:55,575 --> 01:14:56,950
What do you think?

873
01:15:01,372 --> 01:15:03,748
You need a new pair of boots.

874
01:15:04,417 --> 01:15:06,710
Your other ones are very worn.

875
01:15:07,795 --> 01:15:10,088
I cleaned them last night.

876
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:57,469
Now, there's His Lordship, hmm?

877
01:15:57,595 --> 01:15:59,596
- He's shaking in his breeches.
- Yeah.

878
01:15:59,680 --> 01:16:01,681
Fine day for it!

879
01:16:14,820 --> 01:16:16,279
Come on!

880
01:16:16,364 --> 01:16:21,534
Come on then, lads.
Get in there and open the doors.

881
01:16:26,499 --> 01:16:29,209
Get them all off. Quick as you can.

882
01:16:39,345 --> 01:16:42,681
What's going on here?
This is private property!

883
01:16:42,807 --> 01:16:44,766
Get off before we call the guards!

884
01:16:44,850 --> 01:16:47,644
Shush your trap
and get you back to the big house!

885
01:16:47,728 --> 01:16:49,312
This is my home, my family's home.

886
01:16:49,397 --> 01:16:52,691
I heard there was loads of room
up in Gralton Hall. Go up there for you.

887
01:16:52,817 --> 01:16:54,818
No more evictions without just cause.

888
01:16:54,902 --> 01:16:57,529
All these people are going to jail,
I promise you that!

889
01:16:57,655 --> 01:16:59,906
Go back!

890
01:17:00,866 --> 01:17:04,869
Down on your knees! Get on your knees!

891
01:17:08,374 --> 01:17:13,920
If you... If you or your earl or anyone
lays a hand on this family,

892
01:17:14,046 --> 01:17:16,339
you'll get what's coming to you.
Do you hear me?

893
01:17:16,424 --> 01:17:19,217
You're to leave these people in peace
in their own home!

894
01:17:19,343 --> 01:17:22,178
- You won't get away with this.
- I will get away with it.

895
01:17:25,516 --> 01:17:28,393
There's to be
no more evictions on this estate!

896
01:17:31,355 --> 01:17:34,566
Come on, put the rest of the stuff
back into this house. Come on.

897
01:17:45,870 --> 01:17:47,078
A chairde!

898
01:17:47,955 --> 01:17:51,708
I want to introduce to you a man
whom all of us know,

899
01:17:51,792 --> 01:17:54,919
whom all of us trust
and have confidence in.

900
01:17:55,755 --> 01:17:58,298
Jimmy Gralton, come up here
and say a few words.

901
01:17:58,424 --> 01:18:00,884
Go on, Jimmy.

902
01:18:05,806 --> 01:18:07,932
Friends, comrades.

903
01:18:09,268 --> 01:18:14,314
Who could not appreciate
the magnificence of the mansion we passed?

904
01:18:14,440 --> 01:18:17,400
Fertile land as far as the eye can see.

905
01:18:17,985 --> 01:18:21,446
And the simplicity of this cottage.

906
01:18:21,572 --> 01:18:23,615
The Earl snaps his fingers,

907
01:18:23,741 --> 01:18:26,743
and our brother and sister here
and their five children

908
01:18:26,827 --> 01:18:28,453
are thrown onto the street.

909
01:18:29,955 --> 01:18:34,167
This is the greatest lie
they try to stuff down our throats,

910
01:18:34,293 --> 01:18:38,046
that Ireland is one,
that our nation is one,

911
01:18:38,130 --> 01:18:40,090
and that we are all one people,

912
01:18:40,174 --> 01:18:43,134
united in our beliefs
with one common interest.

913
01:18:44,845 --> 01:18:48,098
But do you think the interests
of a child in the slum

914
01:18:48,182 --> 01:18:50,850
are the same
as the rack-renting landlord?

915
01:18:51,769 --> 01:18:55,230
Do you think the interests of a labourer
are the same as the Earl's?

916
01:18:55,314 --> 01:18:56,481
No.

917
01:18:56,607 --> 01:18:59,651
The interests of a miner
or a factory worker

918
01:18:59,777 --> 01:19:04,114
the same as the owner's, his bankers',
his lawyers', his investors'

919
01:19:04,198 --> 01:19:07,659
and the prostitute journalists'
hired to write their lies?

920
01:19:07,785 --> 01:19:09,119
Some here today.

921
01:19:09,203 --> 01:19:13,289
Do you think they give a damn about our old,

922
01:19:13,374 --> 01:19:16,668
the sick, the unemployed,
the hungry, the homeless,

923
01:19:16,794 --> 01:19:20,505
and those forced to leave our shores
desperate for work?

924
01:19:21,507 --> 01:19:24,968
I saw the '20s in New York,
with my own eyes,

925
01:19:25,052 --> 01:19:29,514
and the wild speculation and greed
that infected everyone.

926
01:19:29,807 --> 01:19:32,058
And then I saw the bubble burst.

927
01:19:32,184 --> 01:19:36,646
The crash of '29
and misery in a land of plenty.

928
01:19:36,730 --> 01:19:39,816
Let's not forget
how it spread round the world,

929
01:19:39,900 --> 01:19:44,654
from a system steeped in illusion,
exploitation and avarice.

930
01:19:44,864 --> 01:19:50,577
They tried to pretend
that it was destiny or an act of God,

931
01:19:50,703 --> 01:19:52,579
but it was all man-made.

932
01:19:54,540 --> 01:19:58,418
We need to take control
of our lives again.

933
01:19:58,544 --> 01:20:01,588
Work for need, not for greed.

934
01:20:01,714 --> 01:20:06,759
And not just to survive like a dog,
but to live and to celebrate.

935
01:20:06,886 --> 01:20:07,886
Yes!

936
01:20:08,012 --> 01:20:13,016
And to dance, to sing,
as free human beings.

937
01:20:16,187 --> 01:20:18,229
Now, on you go into your home.

938
01:21:14,286 --> 01:21:16,913
Everybody down! Everybody down!

939
01:21:18,624 --> 01:21:20,833
Everybody down! Get down!

940
01:21:20,960 --> 01:21:22,544
- Stay down!
- Everybody down!

941
01:21:22,628 --> 01:21:26,089
Stay down everyone.
Keep your heads down.

942
01:21:26,173 --> 01:21:28,299
Everybody's fine.

943
01:21:28,425 --> 01:21:30,218
Anyone hurt?

944
01:21:30,302 --> 01:21:32,428
Stay where you are, stay where you are.

945
01:21:32,513 --> 01:21:34,097
Keep your heads down!

946
01:21:36,517 --> 01:21:38,726
Stay down,
stay down, stay down.

947
01:21:38,811 --> 01:21:42,689
- Is everyone all right?
- Now you're gonna have to watch your back.

948
01:21:47,861 --> 01:21:49,696
Now it's started, Jimmy.

949
01:21:51,031 --> 01:21:52,824
Cowardly bastards.

950
01:21:53,701 --> 01:21:58,329
Is that a truck driving off, you hear that?

951
01:21:59,999 --> 01:22:04,210
I see no lights, but I'm sure that was a
truck driving off there. D'you hear it?

952
01:22:05,671 --> 01:22:08,673
- I can't be sure.
- Bastards!

953
01:22:10,009 --> 01:22:11,718
Cowards, huh?

954
01:22:11,844 --> 01:22:15,179
The hall's full of women and children.

955
01:22:49,340 --> 01:22:51,549
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

956
01:22:51,675 --> 01:22:54,677
It is over 25 years
since my last confession.

957
01:22:55,095 --> 01:22:57,930
I would like your advice
on what to do with the Pharisees who,

958
01:22:58,057 --> 01:23:00,975
from the safe distance of the pulpit,
have told lies,

959
01:23:01,060 --> 01:23:04,354
incited hatred
and encouraged the rifle squad

960
01:23:04,438 --> 01:23:07,190
to attack and endanger
the lives of innocent people.

961
01:23:07,274 --> 01:23:09,025
What are you talking about?

962
01:23:09,109 --> 01:23:11,361
I would like your advice
on the sin of pride,

963
01:23:11,445 --> 01:23:14,113
on those who assume
they are the fount of all knowledge,

964
01:23:14,239 --> 01:23:17,200
and yet do nothing but promote
ignorance and superstition.

965
01:23:17,284 --> 01:23:18,951
Do you want confession?

966
01:23:19,078 --> 01:23:21,913
And those who try to destroy
what is best in us,

967
01:23:22,039 --> 01:23:25,875
our imagination, our sense of fun,
by threats of damnation.

968
01:23:25,959 --> 01:23:31,130
But worst of all, those who try to kill
our spirit by their miserable drabness,

969
01:23:31,256 --> 01:23:35,551
who have such venom in their hearts
for everything they cannot control.

970
01:23:35,636 --> 01:23:38,012
Gralton, this is a sacrilege.

971
01:23:38,097 --> 01:23:41,391
No, I'll tell you what the sacrilege is,
Reverend Father.

972
01:23:41,934 --> 01:23:44,769
Having more hate in your heart
than love.

973
01:23:53,612 --> 01:23:54,946
Goodnight, Mary.

974
01:23:56,115 --> 01:23:58,866
Can I ask you something, Father Seamus?

975
01:23:58,951 --> 01:24:00,410
You can, of course.

976
01:24:00,911 --> 01:24:03,746
Do you think Father Sheridan
is his usual self?

977
01:24:03,831 --> 01:24:07,792
It's Gralton.
He's obsessed with the man.

978
01:24:09,294 --> 01:24:12,588
Oh, don't worry about it, Mary.
Goodnight.

979
01:24:12,673 --> 01:24:14,006
Goodnight.

980
01:24:41,827 --> 01:24:43,035
Come in.

981
01:24:44,163 --> 01:24:45,621
Have a wee drop.

982
01:24:54,298 --> 01:24:55,631
There you are.

983
01:24:56,717 --> 01:24:58,176
Slainte.

984
01:24:59,011 --> 01:25:00,470
Slainte.

985
01:25:03,891 --> 01:25:06,058
What's wrong with that, huh?

986
01:25:09,730 --> 01:25:12,899
You know,
that's the voice of a black woman.

987
01:25:13,358 --> 01:25:14,400
Yeah.

988
01:25:15,527 --> 01:25:17,403
Quite remarkable, huh?

989
01:25:21,241 --> 01:25:23,242
Oh, Gralton came today.

990
01:25:24,203 --> 01:25:28,289
He had the nerve to leave these records
outside in the porch.

991
01:25:28,373 --> 01:25:31,125
And he had the guts to face me
in the confessional.

992
01:25:31,210 --> 01:25:33,878
D'you know what he said? Hmm?

993
01:25:34,880 --> 01:25:40,384
He said, "You have more hate
in your heart than love."

994
01:25:42,346 --> 01:25:44,180
What do you make of that?

995
01:26:43,615 --> 01:26:48,786
Will it be you next, son?
I'm so worried for you.

996
01:27:24,448 --> 01:27:29,827
Listen, what you've learned is in
your heads forever. They can't destroy that.

997
01:27:52,684 --> 01:27:53,684
Thank you.

998
01:27:54,519 --> 01:27:58,189
These are the tactics
of the Ku Klux Klan. No, thank you.

999
01:28:00,859 --> 01:28:03,945
Cowardice, sneaking around
in the middle of the night.

1000
01:28:04,029 --> 01:28:06,697
Strikes me they were keen
to avoid loss of life.

1001
01:28:06,823 --> 01:28:08,157
Thank you.

1002
01:28:12,162 --> 01:28:14,205
- Slainte.
- Slainte.

1003
01:28:14,331 --> 01:28:15,998
To the business ahead.

1004
01:28:17,376 --> 01:28:19,877
So, have they
found the culprits yet?

1005
01:28:20,003 --> 01:28:23,214
As you know, Father, Gralton
had quite a few enemies in the locality.

1006
01:28:23,298 --> 01:28:25,049
He had a lot of friends, too,

1007
01:28:25,175 --> 01:28:27,218
despite our best efforts.

1008
01:28:27,886 --> 01:28:30,388
It's disgusting behaviour.
What are we gonna do next?

1009
01:28:30,514 --> 01:28:33,641
Are we gonna burn down the cottage
with the old woman inside?

1010
01:28:33,892 --> 01:28:36,727
Make no mistake,
it's a disaster for the community.

1011
01:28:36,812 --> 01:28:39,689
And we'll all be the losers
because of it.

1012
01:28:40,065 --> 01:28:42,483
It would be a tragedy
if we turned him into a martyr.

1013
01:28:42,567 --> 01:28:43,985
That would be a huge mistake.

1014
01:28:44,069 --> 01:28:45,987
It'd be a tragedy for a decent man

1015
01:28:46,071 --> 01:28:50,241
to get shot in the back
and lose his life, Mr O'Keefe!

1016
01:28:51,535 --> 01:28:53,411
"Is it Christ or Gralton?"

1017
01:28:53,537 --> 01:28:56,414
I think those were the words of
several parish priests...

1018
01:28:56,498 --> 01:28:58,165
I suspect if Christ was here today,

1019
01:28:58,250 --> 01:29:00,084
there'd be several members of this parish

1020
01:29:00,210 --> 01:29:03,504
who would have Him crucified again.
That's what I suspect!

1021
01:29:03,588 --> 01:29:07,925
Cut out the nonsense. I expect
he'll scamper away sooner or later.

1022
01:29:08,051 --> 01:29:11,595
He's a bloody communist.
They don't scamper like you lot.

1023
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:15,433
They might make a tactical retreat,
but they'll fight till their last breath.

1024
01:29:15,559 --> 01:29:19,270
Look what they're doing in Belfast.
This is incredible.

1025
01:29:19,354 --> 01:29:23,190
Read that.
"The Falls and Shankill Unite."

1026
01:29:23,275 --> 01:29:27,236
Stirring up fraternity between poor
Catholics and unemployed Protestants.

1027
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:31,282
I'm not clear.
Is that a good thing now or a bad thing?

1028
01:29:31,366 --> 01:29:33,200
20,000 strikers.

1029
01:29:33,285 --> 01:29:35,870
They even fought against police
issued with 800 rifles.

1030
01:29:35,954 --> 01:29:40,041
Two killed, Father, and 70 injured.
Over 100,000 on the streets.

1031
01:29:40,125 --> 01:29:42,960
Protestants and Catholics
united at the funerals.

1032
01:29:43,045 --> 01:29:47,715
Workers challenging the leaders of
their own trade unions as sell-outs.

1033
01:29:47,799 --> 01:29:50,217
- That's the Reds for you.
- No, that's poverty!

1034
01:29:50,302 --> 01:29:53,804
- Don't be so goddamn naive!
- Calm down, gentlemen.

1035
01:29:53,930 --> 01:29:55,556
I apologise for raising my voice.

1036
01:29:55,640 --> 01:29:59,560
Speaking of Belfast. Tom Mann.

1037
01:30:00,771 --> 01:30:03,147
And what's he got to do with us
and our problem?

1038
01:30:12,949 --> 01:30:15,117
Mr. Gralton. You're under arrest.

1039
01:30:16,161 --> 01:30:17,661
What for?

1040
01:30:17,746 --> 01:30:21,499
I've an order here signed personally
by a member of Cabinet.

1041
01:30:21,583 --> 01:30:25,920
You are to be deported from the country,
forthwith, as an illegal alien.

1042
01:30:26,004 --> 01:30:28,672
Illegal alien?
Have you been drinking, officer?

1043
01:30:28,757 --> 01:30:30,841
- Watch your mouth.
- An alien?

1044
01:30:30,967 --> 01:30:32,009
Sorry, Mrs. Gralton.

1045
01:30:32,135 --> 01:30:35,179
He was born in this house.
He's my son.

1046
01:30:35,263 --> 01:30:37,515
He also holds an American passport,
Mrs. Gralton.

1047
01:30:37,599 --> 01:30:39,016
Let me see that.

1048
01:30:40,310 --> 01:30:42,353
This is terrible.

1049
01:30:42,437 --> 01:30:44,438
- All the way from Dublin?
- It is.

1050
01:30:45,524 --> 01:30:47,274
Minister of Justice.

1051
01:30:50,362 --> 01:30:51,695
What date is the hearing?

1052
01:30:51,780 --> 01:30:55,449
There'll be no hearing for you,
Mr. Gralton. It's a deportation order.

1053
01:30:55,534 --> 01:30:57,952
- He's not a criminal.
- Come on.

1054
01:30:58,036 --> 01:31:00,037
No, you can't take my son.

1055
01:31:00,163 --> 01:31:03,040
I'm sorry, Mrs. Gralton,
we're under strict instructions.

1056
01:31:03,166 --> 01:31:05,459
Sorry, we're under strict instructions
to take him in.

1057
01:31:05,544 --> 01:31:09,130
Well, let him change his jacket.
And let me say goodbye to my son.

1058
01:31:09,214 --> 01:31:10,339
You have two minutes.

1059
01:31:22,727 --> 01:31:24,645
Get up those stairs and watch that door.

1060
01:31:24,729 --> 01:31:26,021
Yes, sir.

1061
01:31:28,859 --> 01:31:31,861
I've made some tea.
You're welcome to a tea.

1062
01:31:32,904 --> 01:31:34,196
Thanks, Mrs. Gralton.

1063
01:31:49,421 --> 01:31:52,423
Mrs. Gralton, I remember
when I was a young fella,

1064
01:31:52,507 --> 01:31:54,925
you used to bring books
round our school.

1065
01:31:55,427 --> 01:31:58,429
- What school was that?
- Sacred Heart.

1066
01:31:58,555 --> 01:32:01,432
It was the best part of the month.
We all looked forward to that.

1067
01:32:01,558 --> 01:32:03,934
Treasure Island, now, was my favourite.

1068
01:32:04,019 --> 01:32:07,438
Robert Louis Stevenson.
It was always very popular.

1069
01:32:07,564 --> 01:32:10,024
I always liked
White Fang meself.

1070
01:32:13,695 --> 01:32:17,114
What's going on, son?
What's going on here?

1071
01:32:18,575 --> 01:32:24,288
We were told that the British deported
a fella in Belfast called Tom Mann,

1072
01:32:24,372 --> 01:32:29,210
some English trade union activist
over to agitate,

1073
01:32:29,294 --> 01:32:32,379
start a general strike
after those workers were shot.

1074
01:32:32,464 --> 01:32:36,300
No trial? That's some "fair play".

1075
01:32:36,384 --> 01:32:40,971
So somebody can be taken away
from their own home without a trial

1076
01:32:41,097 --> 01:32:42,723
or being allowed to have a say?

1077
01:32:42,807 --> 01:32:44,808
Mr. Gralton!

1078
01:32:45,310 --> 01:32:48,312
Mr. Gralton. Are you ready yet?

1079
01:32:49,147 --> 01:32:50,272
Get up there.

1080
01:32:51,107 --> 01:32:53,150
What's going on?

1081
01:32:53,276 --> 01:32:55,653
- Door's jammed.
- Then break it down.

1082
01:32:55,779 --> 01:32:57,905
It's stuck. He's got something...

1083
01:32:57,989 --> 01:33:00,241
Put your back into it,
it's only a small door.

1084
01:33:03,411 --> 01:33:05,746
He's gone
through the feckin' thatch!

1085
01:33:05,830 --> 01:33:07,623
What do you mean he's gone?

1086
01:33:08,667 --> 01:33:11,168
There he is!
He's off across the fields!

1087
01:33:11,253 --> 01:33:12,670
Jesus' sake!

1088
01:33:13,588 --> 01:33:15,256
Shower of useless bastards!

1089
01:33:15,340 --> 01:33:18,133
I'm gonna get youse all fired, I swear.

1090
01:33:20,845 --> 01:33:22,429
Where's the key, Mrs Gralton?

1091
01:33:22,514 --> 01:33:24,848
I don't know. Don't know where I put it.

1092
01:33:24,933 --> 01:33:27,351
Oh, shite! Smash it through!

1093
01:33:29,688 --> 01:33:30,771
Feckin' door!

1094
01:33:30,855 --> 01:33:33,274
- Please, Mrs Gralton.
- I don't know where I put it.

1095
01:33:33,358 --> 01:33:36,110
- They'll have our guts for garters!
- I can't help that.

1096
01:33:36,194 --> 01:33:38,195
Come on!
Get yourself through.

1097
01:33:38,321 --> 01:33:40,781
- What's going on here?
- Breathe in.

1098
01:33:40,865 --> 01:33:43,200
- What's going on here?
- The feckin' door is locked!

1099
01:33:43,285 --> 01:33:45,202
- Where's the key?
- Down her drawers!

1100
01:33:45,287 --> 01:33:48,539
He's out the back,
he went through the roof.

1101
01:33:48,873 --> 01:33:52,209
You get after him,
you gobshite! He's round the back!

1102
01:33:52,335 --> 01:33:53,877
Get after him, would you?

1103
01:33:55,547 --> 01:33:58,132
Get up, you eejit,
and get after him, for God's sake.

1104
01:33:58,216 --> 01:33:59,466
Will I pull you out, sir?

1105
01:33:59,551 --> 01:34:02,886
What are you coming back to me for?
You should be going after him!

1106
01:34:20,739 --> 01:34:23,741
Sean Maguire! Come out, Sean Maguire!

1107
01:34:23,867 --> 01:34:27,036
Get out of my fucking house!
What the hell are you doing?

1108
01:34:27,162 --> 01:34:29,663
- Get out! Get out!
- Out you come.

1109
01:34:29,748 --> 01:34:32,166
Jesus Christ! Bastards!

1110
01:34:32,250 --> 01:34:36,045
- Where's Jimmy? Where's Jimmy Gralton?
- Get off me!

1111
01:34:36,171 --> 01:34:38,255
- Get off me!
- Put your hands up!

1112
01:34:38,381 --> 01:34:40,883
- God, you fuckers!
- Get the cuffs on him.

1113
01:34:41,885 --> 01:34:43,427
- House empty.
- Fuck.

1114
01:34:43,511 --> 01:34:45,346
- Where's Jimmy, Sean?
- I don't fucking know!

1115
01:34:45,430 --> 01:34:47,097
- Where is he?
- I don't know!

1116
01:34:47,223 --> 01:34:49,433
Get off me! You're hurting me!

1117
01:34:49,517 --> 01:34:52,603
Get out! Stay away from my children!

1118
01:34:52,729 --> 01:34:54,271
You stay away from my children!

1119
01:34:54,356 --> 01:34:56,023
Come out, Mossie!

1120
01:34:57,859 --> 01:34:59,526
- Get out!
- Where is he?

1121
01:34:59,611 --> 01:35:01,695
- Where's who?
- Where's Gralton?

1122
01:35:01,780 --> 01:35:05,783
What's going on?
Leave him alone. Leave him alone!

1123
01:35:05,867 --> 01:35:08,786
He's away in Dublin
having a pint with de Valera!

1124
01:35:45,240 --> 01:35:47,324
- Whoa.
- Ah, Tommy Gilroy.

1125
01:35:47,450 --> 01:35:48,826
Whoa, Dixie. Whoa.

1126
01:35:48,952 --> 01:35:51,578
Stop there now.
We're gonna have a look around, OK?

1127
01:35:51,663 --> 01:35:53,664
That's fine. What are you looking for?

1128
01:35:53,790 --> 01:35:56,333
- What is it you're looking for?
- What's in the hay, Tommy?

1129
01:35:56,459 --> 01:35:58,669
- How are you, Tommy?
- Doherty.

1130
01:35:58,795 --> 01:36:01,588
- Where's Gralton, Tommy?
- I don't know where Gralton is.

1131
01:36:01,673 --> 01:36:05,008
Leave my hay alone. You won't find him
in there, whatever you do.

1132
01:36:05,093 --> 01:36:07,344
- Sweeney, let me away up the road.
- What's your rush?

1133
01:36:07,429 --> 01:36:11,098
I have no rush. I'm just trying to do
a man's job and just take me hay home.

1134
01:36:11,599 --> 01:36:14,601
I don't have James Gralton.
Let me away up the road, Sweeney!

1135
01:36:19,149 --> 01:36:22,443
Gentlemen.
Sean, great to see you.

1136
01:36:22,527 --> 01:36:25,279
- You all right?
- Aye. Hanging in there.

1137
01:36:25,363 --> 01:36:26,947
I'm freezing.

1138
01:36:30,118 --> 01:36:32,786
There's some eggs there.
Bread and milk.

1139
01:36:34,330 --> 01:36:36,039
Good man.

1140
01:36:37,667 --> 01:36:42,379
- You're still in one piece anyway.
- Still breathing.

1141
01:37:12,994 --> 01:37:14,411
We're here now.

1142
01:37:26,341 --> 01:37:30,052
The town hall was packed
for the meeting. Two to a seat.

1143
01:37:30,720 --> 01:37:34,264
We presented the letters of support
from around the country first.

1144
01:37:34,599 --> 01:37:39,019
But what really infuriated them
were the petitions from America.

1145
01:37:39,103 --> 01:37:41,271
The Mayor was there all puffed up,

1146
01:37:41,397 --> 01:37:45,526
and one eejit talked about a communist plot
to nationalise women and children.

1147
01:37:47,612 --> 01:37:49,446
They didn't want to let
your mother speak,

1148
01:37:49,572 --> 01:37:53,200
but the gallery started chanting
"fair play", so they gave in.

1149
01:37:56,454 --> 01:37:58,914
Her hands were shaking
holding her notes.

1150
01:37:59,582 --> 01:38:01,708
But her voice was steady.

1151
01:38:02,544 --> 01:38:04,628
You should have seen
the look in her eye.

1152
01:38:09,133 --> 01:38:12,135
"What can a mother say
when about to lose a son?

1153
01:38:13,429 --> 01:38:17,057
"Part of me wants to scream again
as in childbirth,

1154
01:38:17,725 --> 01:38:21,728
"and part of me wants to ask
'What is his crime? '.

1155
01:38:21,813 --> 01:38:24,648
"Why is an old tin hall so dangerous?

1156
01:38:26,609 --> 01:38:28,986
"Am I to blame for giving him books,

1157
01:38:29,112 --> 01:38:31,822
"teaching the boy to think
and ask questions?

1158
01:38:34,158 --> 01:38:38,161
"He brought back the world
which he had seen to the hall he built.

1159
01:38:39,122 --> 01:38:40,664
"Is that the crime?

1160
01:38:40,748 --> 01:38:45,002
"If we can take a man
from his home without a trial,

1161
01:38:45,086 --> 01:38:47,754
"send him off because of
what is in his head.

1162
01:38:50,133 --> 01:38:54,511
"I may lose my child,
but Ireland loses much, much more."

1163
01:38:56,389 --> 01:38:57,848
The gallery cheered.

1164
01:38:59,642 --> 01:39:01,476
The Council ignored her.

1165
01:39:03,396 --> 01:39:06,607
They took the letters of support
and they burned them outside.

1166
01:39:09,277 --> 01:39:11,903
All those meetings
up and down the country.

1167
01:39:13,364 --> 01:39:17,784
The truth is, your support is confined
to the trade unions and usual friends.

1168
01:39:18,620 --> 01:39:21,872
The IRA are even on the fence.
They don't want to upset the Church.

1169
01:39:21,956 --> 01:39:23,790
And the deportation stands.

1170
01:39:26,669 --> 01:39:29,129
Father Seamus came to see me.

1171
01:39:29,213 --> 01:39:31,965
He fears it'll turn the youth
against the Church.

1172
01:39:32,050 --> 01:39:34,551
I prefer the Sheridans.

1173
01:39:34,636 --> 01:39:37,471
At least he has the courage
of his convictions.

1174
01:39:37,555 --> 01:39:41,183
He said he'd go over Sheridan's head
to talk to the bishop.

1175
01:39:41,267 --> 01:39:43,644
He'd even go to Dublin
to try and make peace.

1176
01:39:44,937 --> 01:39:46,188
If?

1177
01:39:47,315 --> 01:39:49,775
If you promised
not to build the hall again.

1178
01:39:51,194 --> 01:39:53,737
And lived a quiet, private life.

1179
01:40:23,309 --> 01:40:25,352
A quiet, private life.

1180
01:40:27,397 --> 01:40:28,939
With you, Oonagh.

1181
01:40:35,947 --> 01:40:38,949
I wish with all my heart
we had another life to live.

1182
01:40:44,622 --> 01:40:49,126
Jimmy, they've drafted in more soldiers.
By the dozen.

1183
01:40:50,545 --> 01:40:52,838
It's only a matter of time.

1184
01:40:54,382 --> 01:40:56,174
God, this hurts so much.

1185
01:41:01,723 --> 01:41:04,891
These are our last moments, I know it.

1186
01:41:07,061 --> 01:41:09,104
I'm never gonna see you again.

1187
01:41:43,139 --> 01:41:44,514
Gardai! Gardai!

1188
01:41:44,599 --> 01:41:46,933
Don't move, Jimmy, don't move!
Don't move!

1189
01:41:47,018 --> 01:41:50,395
We have you now, you dirty bastard, ya!
We have you now, boy!

1190
01:41:50,480 --> 01:41:53,940
We have you now, Jimmy!
There'll be no getting away this time!

1191
01:41:54,317 --> 01:41:56,985
Let him stand up.

1192
01:41:58,404 --> 01:42:00,071
Come on now. Out.

1193
01:42:01,115 --> 01:42:03,825
What's going on here?
Get out of my house!

1194
01:42:13,795 --> 01:42:16,046
We're nearly done here.
Thanks.

1195
01:42:17,340 --> 01:42:20,592
Three pounds, nine shillings
and thrupence ha'penny, Sergeant.

1196
01:42:20,676 --> 01:42:22,594
- Is that all you have?
- Aye.

1197
01:42:23,846 --> 01:42:26,389
And the good news is
we don't confiscate it.

1198
01:42:26,474 --> 01:42:29,267
The bad news is it'll be going
towards paying your fare.

1199
01:42:38,778 --> 01:42:40,487
So, how did you find me?

1200
01:42:53,417 --> 01:42:55,460
Can I visit my mother to say goodbye?

1201
01:42:55,545 --> 01:42:57,128
Not a hope in hell.

1202
01:42:57,213 --> 01:42:59,798
She's frail. My last chance to see her.

1203
01:42:59,882 --> 01:43:03,635
I've strict orders to get you out
of here and before the riff-raff come.

1204
01:43:05,429 --> 01:43:08,473
- Where are you taking me?
- You're going straight to Cork,

1205
01:43:08,558 --> 01:43:11,142
and then to Cobh
where we have a ship waiting for you.

1206
01:43:18,276 --> 01:43:21,069
Should have kept your big mouth shut,
Gralton.

1207
01:43:21,153 --> 01:43:24,406
You always had to be cock of the walk.
You had this coming to you.

1208
01:43:24,740 --> 01:43:27,367
Can I have a sheet of paper
to write her a note?

1209
01:43:27,451 --> 01:43:29,786
Save your tears for the crossing.

1210
01:43:29,871 --> 01:43:31,955
There's a fine postal service
from New York.

1211
01:43:32,582 --> 01:43:34,082
There he is.

1212
01:43:41,257 --> 01:43:43,800
- There's the bollocks!
- You antichrist!

1213
01:43:43,885 --> 01:43:46,011
You won't set foot in our land again!

1214
01:43:46,095 --> 01:43:48,388
Good riddance to you Gralton,
you Red bastard.

1215
01:43:50,182 --> 01:43:52,726
You're like Charlie Chaplin
with a jacket on.

1216
01:43:52,810 --> 01:43:56,229
This'll cheer you up. The ship waiting
for you is called the Britannic.

1217
01:43:56,314 --> 01:43:58,189
Please. Please!

1218
01:43:58,274 --> 01:43:59,858
Show the man some respect!

1219
01:43:59,942 --> 01:44:03,695
He has more courage and decency
than all of you put together.

1220
01:44:16,042 --> 01:44:18,043
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

1221
01:44:19,921 --> 01:44:21,463
- Marie.
- Jimmy!

1222
01:44:21,547 --> 01:44:24,591
- Jimmy!
- Marie! Stay where you are!

1223
01:44:25,718 --> 01:44:28,345
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

1224
01:44:32,934 --> 01:44:36,227
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

1225
01:44:36,312 --> 01:44:38,897
- Get back, you little fecker!
- Get back!

1226
01:44:38,981 --> 01:44:41,107
Go on, clear off!

1227
01:44:48,074 --> 01:44:50,075
- Clear off, the lot of you!
- BOY: Jimmy!

1228
01:44:50,159 --> 01:44:52,035
Clear off!

1229
01:44:52,954 --> 01:44:54,913
You're under arrest for kidnap!

1230
01:44:56,916 --> 01:44:59,250
Get off the road
or we'll run you over.

1231
01:44:59,335 --> 01:45:00,669
Go home!

1232
01:45:00,795 --> 01:45:03,004
Get off the road. Get off the road!

1233
01:45:05,466 --> 01:45:06,800
Get away from him.

1234
01:45:06,884 --> 01:45:10,095
- Don't let the bastards get you!
- We won't stop dancing.

1235
01:45:10,179 --> 01:45:13,807
- Don't forget to send us more records.
- We'll keep dancing and dreaming.

1236
01:45:13,891 --> 01:45:16,768
I'm gonna teach my daughter
the shim sham. We'll miss you.

1237
01:45:16,852 --> 01:45:19,562
- You'll write to us?
- I'll send you back money for a party.

1238
01:45:19,647 --> 01:45:21,982
Get this truck going.

1239
01:45:22,066 --> 01:45:24,985
- You're a good man, Jimmy!
- Don't forget us, Jimmy.

1240
01:45:25,069 --> 01:45:28,446
- You won't forget us, Jimmy, will you?
- Drive over 'em!

1241
01:45:28,531 --> 01:45:31,324
Get off the road!
Get off the road! Get off the road!

1242
01:45:31,409 --> 01:45:33,159
Get off!

1243
01:45:33,244 --> 01:45:35,203
You don't deserve this, Jimmy!

1244
01:45:39,375 --> 01:45:40,709
Go on, Jimmy.

1245
01:45:45,923 --> 01:45:50,844
I wish, I wish, I wish in vain

1246
01:45:50,928 --> 01:45:55,932
I wish I had my heart again

